					<description><![CDATA[This is a two part post. Part 1: First and foremost, the band &#8220;Disturbed&#8221; is apparently going on an indefinite hiatus after they conclude the Rockstar Energy Mayhem festival. Â I&#8217;ll be seeing them play in Detroit with mixed emotions. On one hand, this is a band that has produced alot of very good music. Â On [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This is a two part post.</p>
<p><strong>Part 1:</strong><br />
First and foremost, the band &#8220;Disturbed&#8221; is apparently going on an indefinite hiatus after they conclude the Rockstar Energy Mayhem festival. Â I&#8217;ll be seeing them play in Detroit with mixed emotions.</p>
<p>On one hand, this is a band that has produced alot of very good music. Â On the other, they&#8217;ve also been the source of jokes and laughs at cheezy sounding grunts/rahs/suack. Â It&#8217;s like their debut album was catchy, but we also made fun of it. Â Their song &#8220;Prayer&#8221; changed everything. Â It was epic and profound. Â No longer the brunt of satire, they carried this respect through Ten Thousand Fists, and through some ofÂ Indestructible. Â However, my unconditional love and respect for this band certainly ceased with the latest album Asylum.</p>
<p>Somehow Disturbed has come full circle in a bad way. Â Back to their laughable and comedic roots, the video for &#8220;Animal&#8221; sealed their fate in my opinion. Â It was cheesy and literally laughable to me. Â I don&#8217;t really fault Disturbed for this; as I&#8217;m sure writing music and lyrics over a decade has it&#8217;s ups and downs. Â I guess I am a little surprised at how far up they were; vs. how low they have come and gone to be.</p>
<p>As Vanlandw honestly and correctly put &#8211; &#8220;Maybe it&#8217;s for the better&#8221;. Â I think I agree, but it does still effect me to know that I&#8217;m seeing Disturbed on what may very well be their very last tour.</p>
<p><strong>Part 2:</strong><br />
I&#8217;m pretty sure I had viral meningitis last week.</p>
